WEBVTT

00:36.569 --> 00:39.138
- Our planet
faces a lot of problems.

00:39.140 --> 00:40.406
But in some parts of the world,

00:40.408 --> 00:43.409
people live in a time
of over-consumption,

00:43.411 --> 00:47.513
abundance of food, and an
eagerness to be fit and healthy.

00:47.515 --> 00:50.082
The supermarket is
overflowing with options.

00:50.084 --> 00:54.153
But despite that, we are
poorly advised in nutrition,

00:54.155 --> 00:56.121
and easily vulnerable
to misinformation,

00:57.490 --> 01:00.592
and unreliable slogans,
inaccurate health promises,

01:00.594 --> 01:02.694
and colorful tempting packages

01:02.696 --> 01:05.364
are cluttering our
relationship with food,

01:05.366 --> 01:07.566
and risking our well-being.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.401
We are bombarded by
conflicting information

01:09.403 --> 01:12.671
about food, diets
and supplements.

01:12.673 --> 01:15.274
So how can we know
what's best for us?

01:15.276 --> 01:17.376
Which foods improve
health, and which ones

01:17.378 --> 01:19.611
can potentially promote disease.

01:19.613 --> 01:22.848
I have struggled with these
questions for a long time.

01:22.850 --> 01:24.850
And it has been a
challenge to find a diet

01:24.852 --> 01:28.287
that would help me
achieve my health goals.

01:28.289 --> 01:30.722
After trying several new
diets over the years,

01:30.724 --> 01:33.559
I decided to change
my lifestyle,

01:33.561 --> 01:35.594
by simply incorporating
lots of plant-based

01:35.596 --> 01:37.729
foods into my diet.

01:37.731 --> 01:40.165
So far, it has worked for me.

01:40.167 --> 01:42.601
I lost 50 pounds, brought
my blood pressure,

01:42.603 --> 01:45.404
blood sugar and
cholesterol under control,

01:45.406 --> 01:47.639
and overall, felt really good.

01:47.641 --> 01:49.208
But it was a work in progress,

01:49.210 --> 01:50.809
and I still had many
questions and concerns

01:50.811 --> 01:54.613
about nutrition and living
this plant-based lifestyle

01:54.615 --> 01:57.583
for the long run,
especially now with a recent

01:57.585 --> 02:00.719
addition to our family, i
felt that I really needed

02:00.721 --> 02:02.688
to find answers.

02:02.690 --> 02:04.590
So I decided to go on a journey,

02:04.592 --> 02:06.358
to search for the
truth, and to uncover

02:06.360 --> 02:09.527
many of the myths
surrounding food.

02:09.530 --> 02:11.697
For three years, I traveled
across the country,

02:11.699 --> 02:14.199
and interviewed the
world's top authorities

02:14.201 --> 02:16.902
on the subject, as well as
people that had experienced

02:16.904 --> 02:20.272
amazing, life changing benefits
through healthy eating.

02:21.641 --> 02:23.642
All to explore the idea
of what is the healthiest

02:23.644 --> 02:27.146
and most sustainable
diet for ourselves,

02:27.148 --> 02:29.715
future generations,
and our planet.

02:31.284 --> 02:33.619
So join me on this journey
of shocking discoveries,

02:33.621 --> 02:36.889
and buckle up, because
what you're about to learn

02:36.891 --> 02:39.191
might forever change the
way you look at the food

02:39.193 --> 02:40.526
on your plate.

02:54.807 --> 02:56.341
- Well, there's a lot
of difference of opinion

02:56.343 --> 02:59.811
about it, and there's
a faction of people

02:59.813 --> 03:01.680
who insist that there
are different diets

03:01.682 --> 03:03.549
for different people.

03:03.551 --> 03:05.250
But I think that the
evidence is fairly clear that

03:05.252 --> 03:06.618
that's not true,
and there really is

03:06.620 --> 03:08.787
an appropriate diet for humans,

03:08.789 --> 03:10.556
just like there's a best
diet for cats, dogs,

03:10.558 --> 03:13.692
elephants, and any other mammal.

03:13.694 --> 03:17.529
And the best diet for humans
is one that is plant-based,

03:17.531 --> 03:20.265
almost all calories
coming from four principle

03:20.267 --> 03:22.301
food groups, fruit,
vegetables, whole grains

03:22.303 --> 03:23.502
and legumes.

03:23.504 --> 03:26.205
It's low in fat, high in fiber.

03:26.207 --> 03:28.307
Not very much processed
food, none is great,

03:28.309 --> 03:30.876
but in today's world, I don't
know how realistic that is.

03:30.878 --> 03:34.680
- What we have seen in
nutrition for many, many years,

03:35.782 --> 03:38.784
I must say, is a
lot of confusion.

03:38.786 --> 03:40.886
You go and survey
people, you know,

03:40.888 --> 03:42.521
outside of the science,
and ask them what do

03:42.523 --> 03:44.556
they think that nutrition is,

03:44.558 --> 03:46.692
and you can hear all
kinds of comments.

03:46.694 --> 03:47.893
I eat this, and I eat that,

03:47.895 --> 03:49.861
and this is good,
and this is not good.

03:49.863 --> 03:51.396
There's also confusion
in the professions.

03:51.398 --> 03:52.998
You know, medical
doctors are not trained

03:53.000 --> 03:54.399
in this field.

03:54.401 --> 03:56.635
And there's confusion
in my own field.

03:56.637 --> 03:58.337
You know, about
medical research.

03:58.339 --> 04:01.240
We don't get an opportunity,
to tell, you know,

04:01.242 --> 04:03.942
the real science I think,
the way it should be told.

04:03.944 --> 04:06.378
Because we're overwhelmed,

04:06.380 --> 04:09.648
with the corporate sector
trying to sell stuff.

04:09.650 --> 04:11.683
- We are living
in extreme times.

04:11.685 --> 04:14.953
Where we have 27% of people
dying of heart disease,

04:14.955 --> 04:18.023
25% of cancer, 10% of stroke,

04:18.024 --> 04:20.291
four or five percent
from diabetes,

04:20.293 --> 04:22.694
the same number for Alzheimer's.

04:22.696 --> 04:25.497
I mean, these are,
in many, many cases,

04:25.499 --> 04:27.766
diseases of
nutritional ignorance,

04:27.768 --> 04:31.403
and diseases that are all
based on our lifestyle choices.

04:31.405 --> 04:32.871
- There are a lot of
different dietary theories

04:32.873 --> 04:36.875
out there, but I think one
fact is kind of indisputable.

04:36.877 --> 04:40.712
Having a diet that is rich
in whole plant-based foods,

04:40.714 --> 04:44.583
is truly a great way to
get you to good health.

04:44.585 --> 04:46.618
- Everywhere I go
around the world,

04:46.620 --> 04:48.453
there's not a single person
I've met that doesn't

04:48.455 --> 04:50.289
know that fruits and
vegetables are good for them.

04:51.057 --> 04:51.056
We all know it.

04:51.058 --> 04:55.060
It's not about the knowing,
it's about the doing.

04:55.062 --> 04:57.396
- There was a time when
there was no heart disease.

04:57.398 --> 05:01.366
No colon cancer, no breast
cancer, no multiple sclerosis,

05:01.368 --> 05:02.934
no inflammatory arthritis.

05:02.936 --> 05:05.704
Of course these days, in
Asia, the middle east,

05:05.706 --> 05:08.540
in central America,
and around the world,

05:08.542 --> 05:10.642
people have become rich.

05:10.644 --> 05:13.045
They have given up
much of their starch,

05:13.047 --> 05:14.946
and they replaced it
with meat and dairy.

05:14.948 --> 05:17.582
Throughout history, rich
people, the royalty,

05:17.584 --> 05:20.952
the pharaohs, the
queens and the kings,

05:20.954 --> 05:24.056
the priests, the
priestesses, the people

05:24.058 --> 05:25.824
that could afford
to eat the meat.

05:25.826 --> 05:29.728
They had artery disease,
they had obesity,

05:29.730 --> 05:30.996
they were sick.

05:30.998 --> 05:32.397
Nothing's changed
except for the number

05:32.399 --> 05:34.566
of kings and queens
living in the world.

05:36.936 --> 05:39.438
- A question
kept coming to my mind.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.540
If plant foods are
so good for us,

05:41.542 --> 05:43.108
and the consumption
of animal products

05:43.110 --> 05:45.811
in excess appears to do us harm,

05:45.813 --> 05:48.447
how about the ancient
populations of people

05:48.449 --> 05:50.515
that survived on
diets based off mostly

05:50.517 --> 05:52.617
meat, eggs and dairy,

05:52.619 --> 05:54.553
and appeared to be healthy?

05:54.555 --> 05:57.556
After all, aren't we known
for being hunter-gatherers?

05:59.826 --> 06:02.861
- All large, successful
populations of people

06:02.863 --> 06:04.763
have gotten the bulk
of their calories

06:04.765 --> 06:07.366
from starch, rice,
corn, potatoes,

06:07.368 --> 06:09.868
and other starches,
breads and so on.

06:09.870 --> 06:13.405
Particularly when you
live near the equator,

06:13.407 --> 06:16.007
as you move north and
south in latitude,

06:16.009 --> 06:18.510
then you end up eating
more animal foods.

06:18.512 --> 06:21.513
And if you get far
north, like for example,

06:21.515 --> 06:24.449
the inuit eskimos, they
are largely carnivores,

06:24.451 --> 06:26.985
because that's what's available.

06:26.987 --> 06:30.522
But that's a small
population of people

06:30.524 --> 06:32.858
that exists on the extremes
of the environment.

06:33.626 --> 06:35.427
That's the exception,

06:35.429 --> 06:36.661
not the rule.

06:38.531 --> 06:40.632
- We have become
the most successful

06:40.634 --> 06:42.901
species on this planet.

06:42.903 --> 06:44.736
No one comes close to us.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.639
We share it with animals,
and insects, and microbes,

06:47.641 --> 06:50.509
and plants, but
we're number one.

06:50.511 --> 06:51.943
And the way we got to number one

06:51.945 --> 06:54.546
was all about survival.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.748
We see in color, i
believe, because fruits

06:56.750 --> 06:58.650
and vegetables are colorful.

06:58.652 --> 07:01.153
Our hand is perfectly
designed to pick,

07:01.155 --> 07:05.490
forge, grab and dig,
peel, and feed ourselves

07:05.492 --> 07:07.125
fruits and vegetables,
nuts, beans and seeds,

07:07.127 --> 07:10.061
plant food, food made
by mother nature.

07:10.063 --> 07:12.731
- This idea that we're
hunter-gatherers,

07:13.633 --> 07:15.200
is true, we're hunter-gatherers.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.669
But mostly, we've
been gatherers.

07:17.671 --> 07:20.639
One of the problems
has to do with sexism.

07:20.641 --> 07:23.708
It has to do with the
fact that the gatherers

07:23.710 --> 07:27.512
were grandparents,
women, and children.

07:27.514 --> 07:30.549
The hunters were men,
and they got the glory.

07:30.551 --> 07:32.150
The people who really
provided the bulk

07:32.152 --> 07:35.687
of the calories, for most
of the civilizations,

07:35.689 --> 07:38.523
through all verifiable
human history,

07:38.525 --> 07:41.726
have been the women,
children and grandparents.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.596
- Even when i
began considering the idea

07:44.598 --> 07:47.065
of eating mostly a
plant-based diet,

07:47.067 --> 07:49.701
I was still hounded
with many questions.

07:49.703 --> 07:51.203
How was I going
to be able to live

07:51.205 --> 07:53.505
without animal foods?

07:53.507 --> 07:55.607
I didn't want to become
nutrient deficient.

07:55.609 --> 07:57.709
And how about things
like protein, calcium,

07:57.711 --> 07:59.544
and omega 3's?

07:59.546 --> 08:01.913
In my head, I always
associated these nutrients

08:01.915 --> 08:03.849
with animal foods.

08:03.851 --> 08:05.851
I needed to find out
if those were valid

08:05.853 --> 08:08.186
concerns, or simply myths.

08:16.229 --> 08:18.897
- It's almost
impossible to design

08:19.699 --> 08:21.800
a protein deficient diet

08:21.802 --> 08:24.002
surrounding, you know, a variety

08:24.004 --> 08:26.605
of whole plant foods.

08:26.607 --> 08:28.607
- What people need to know

08:28.609 --> 08:31.710
is there's never been a
case of protein deficiency

08:31.712 --> 08:33.511
ever described in
the world literature,

08:33.514 --> 08:35.914
on any natural diet,

08:35.916 --> 08:38.683
that met the sufficient
amount of calories.

08:38.684 --> 08:40.150
- You know, back to
1839 when protein

08:40.153 --> 08:44.022
was discovered, it had
this incredible reverence

08:44.024 --> 08:47.259
associated with it, and
it just gained traction.

08:47.261 --> 08:49.261
But the evidence is
very clear that humans

08:49.263 --> 08:51.897
do not need to eat
a lot of protein,

08:51.899 --> 08:54.566
and when they do, they get
a lot of health problems

08:54.568 --> 08:54.566
as a result.

08:54.568 --> 08:58.703
I mean human protein needs
are just a tiny percentage

08:58.705 --> 09:01.106
of calories, maybe two
and a half, three percent

09:01.108 --> 09:02.307
of calories.

09:02.309 --> 09:04.609
And if you were to
eat the lowest protein

09:04.611 --> 09:06.845
foods, in the plant world,

09:06.847 --> 09:08.113
which would be foods like rice,

09:08.115 --> 09:10.048
you're at eight or
nine percent protein.

09:10.050 --> 09:12.918
So you're not going to
become protein deficient.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.086
But, the promoters of
the low-carb diets,

09:15.088 --> 09:17.122
the promoters of
the sports drinks,

09:17.124 --> 09:19.858
and the food bars, and
all these kinds of things,

09:19.860 --> 09:22.227
insist and market to
the public that they

09:22.229 --> 09:24.262
absolutely must
have more protein.

09:24.264 --> 09:25.664
It's just not true.

09:25.666 --> 09:27.799
In practical sense,
and in reality,

09:27.801 --> 09:29.668
the way we humans operate,

09:29.670 --> 09:32.037
we get ideal loads of
protein if we just get it

09:32.039 --> 09:33.738
from plants.

09:33.740 --> 09:36.641
When we consume animal foods,

09:36.643 --> 09:38.977
to get that protein,
if you will,

09:38.979 --> 09:41.746
what we're actually
doing, we're displacing,

09:41.748 --> 09:43.882
the consumption of
those foods that matter.

09:44.984 --> 09:47.719
And foods that
matter are plants.

09:47.721 --> 09:49.621
- The amount of
animal protein we eat

09:49.623 --> 09:50.822
is the problem.

09:50.824 --> 09:51.790
You know, in rural China,

09:51.792 --> 09:53.792
and Japanese populations,

09:53.794 --> 09:55.327
and healthier
places in the world,

09:55.329 --> 09:55.327
people eat a little
bit of animal protein,

09:55.329 --> 10:00.231
but for economic reasons,
it's very, very, very tiny.

10:00.233 --> 10:01.766
They use one little
piece of meat,

10:01.768 --> 10:03.835
they slice it up,
and it seasons a dish

10:03.837 --> 10:05.103
for eight people.

10:05.105 --> 10:07.072
Here in this country,
we have one gargantuan

10:07.074 --> 10:09.808
piece of meat, we
put it on a plate,

10:09.810 --> 10:11.843
with a tiny little
bit of vegetables,

10:11.845 --> 10:13.378
we call that a meal.

10:13.380 --> 10:16.848
The problem is that when
you eat too much protein,

10:16.850 --> 10:18.817
of any type, you
stress your kidneys,

10:18.819 --> 10:22.354
you stress your liver, and
when it's animal protein,

10:22.356 --> 10:24.656
you increase your
risk of cancer.

10:24.658 --> 10:27.692
And we see cancer is
geographically distributed.

10:27.694 --> 10:29.828
The more animal food
consumed in a society,

10:29.830 --> 10:32.697
the more cancer, more
heart disease, you get.

10:32.699 --> 10:34.733
- And it's amazing all
the animals that we choose

10:34.735 --> 10:38.670
in this country to eat
for protein and calcium,

10:38.672 --> 10:40.238
are vegetarian animals.

10:40.240 --> 10:41.806
Where's the logic in that?

10:41.808 --> 10:43.341
And I always like
to remind you, also,

10:43.343 --> 10:45.110
when you're eating your garbage,

10:45.112 --> 10:46.077
you never ask , "where
am I getting my protein,

10:46.079 --> 10:47.345
"and my calcium."

10:47.347 --> 10:48.813
It's only when you come
into the healthy world

10:48.815 --> 10:50.281
that all of a sudden
you're concerned

10:50.283 --> 10:51.983
with where it's coming from.

10:51.985 --> 10:55.754
- We're in the midst of
this amazing protein push.

10:55.756 --> 10:57.389
Everywhere you look,
the message is clear.

10:57.391 --> 10:58.990
Protein, protein, protein.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.725
This idea that you
need massive amounts

11:00.727 --> 11:03.928
of protein, to
simply breathe air

11:03.930 --> 11:05.063
in and out of your lungs,

11:05.065 --> 11:06.965
you know, and to be healthy,

11:06.967 --> 11:08.933
or to perform as an athlete.

11:08.935 --> 11:10.735
- Prior to making
this dietary change,

11:10.737 --> 11:14.873
like my main nutritional
strategy in a day

11:14.875 --> 11:18.143
was to see how many
grams of protein

11:18.145 --> 11:19.377
I could get in, like about that,

11:19.379 --> 11:21.312
the only calculations
i ever really did,

11:21.314 --> 11:23.181
I didn't count calories,
i didn't count anything,

11:23.183 --> 11:26.084
was just like trying to
get in exorbitant amounts

11:26.086 --> 11:28.453
of grams of protein in my day.

11:28.455 --> 11:30.188
Just because there
are grams of protein

11:30.190 --> 11:31.823
on the nutritional
content of something,

11:31.825 --> 11:33.124
doesn't mean that
your body can actually

11:33.126 --> 11:34.859
process all of those grams.

11:34.861 --> 11:36.194
- Protein does
some other things.

11:36.196 --> 11:37.862
It elevates blood
cholesterol levels,

11:37.864 --> 11:41.399
which most people
have not heard of.

11:41.401 --> 11:44.335
But that's about 100
years old, that idea.

11:44.337 --> 11:45.904
And then repeated several times,

11:45.906 --> 11:47.038
but always ignored.

11:47.040 --> 11:49.908
Animal protein
starts heart disease.

11:49.910 --> 11:52.877
It increases things
like the production

11:52.879 --> 11:54.979
of so called free radicals,

11:54.981 --> 11:57.282
which are those highly
reactive molecules

11:57.284 --> 11:59.851
that actually stimulate aging,

12:00.920 --> 12:02.821
and encourages cancer formation.

12:02.823 --> 12:04.723
It also stimulates the
production of the wrong

12:04.725 --> 12:06.157
kind of hormones.

12:06.159 --> 12:08.159
It tends to increase
the level of estrogens,

12:08.161 --> 12:10.762
for example, and
one, which in turn,

12:10.764 --> 12:12.731
is associated with
breast cancer.

12:12.733 --> 12:14.799
It changes the microflora
in our intestine

12:14.801 --> 12:17.302
when we're consuming
too much protein.

12:17.304 --> 12:18.803
I mean, it does
all these things.

12:18.805 --> 12:20.171
- There's lots of things
we have to worry about

12:20.173 --> 12:22.774
in the American diet.

12:22.776 --> 12:25.744
Fiber, 97% of Americans
don't reach the daily

12:25.746 --> 12:27.178
minimum intake of fiber,

12:27.180 --> 12:29.781
98% of Americans don't
reach the daily minimum

12:29.783 --> 12:32.050
intake of potassium,
for example.

12:32.052 --> 12:33.852
The nutrients of concern
for most Americans

12:33.854 --> 12:36.855
are the ones that are
found in plant foods.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.056
Mostly fruits and vegetables,

12:38.058 --> 12:40.458
and the ones that we're
getting too much of,

12:40.460 --> 12:43.895
in excess, whether
it's calorie, sodium,

12:43.897 --> 12:45.897
cholesterol, saturated
fat, are found

12:45.899 --> 12:48.366
in processed foods and
animal foods in general.

12:50.169 --> 12:51.970
- Many people
decide they want to improve

12:51.972 --> 12:54.873
their health, by staying
away from red meat.

12:54.875 --> 12:57.442
And instead, they begin
consuming more white meats,

12:57.444 --> 13:00.979
like chicken, Turkey, and fish.

13:00.981 --> 13:02.547
I always wondered if
certain types of meats

13:02.549 --> 13:05.350
were really better than others.

13:05.352 --> 13:07.252
- People think that
they're going to be healthy

13:07.254 --> 13:09.821
by giving up red meat,

13:09.823 --> 13:12.190
and instead, eating
poulty and fish.

13:13.292 --> 13:15.059
Stop and think about
this for a minute.

13:15.061 --> 13:18.930
What are meat, poultry and fish?

13:19.565 --> 13:21.466
They're muscles of animals.

13:21.468 --> 13:24.469
In one case, they
have to move a limb,

13:24.471 --> 13:26.538
another case, they flap a wing,

13:26.540 --> 13:28.573
in another case,
they wiggle a tail.

13:28.575 --> 13:30.809
They're the same.

13:30.811 --> 13:33.077
High fat, high protein,

13:33.079 --> 13:36.080
high cholesterol,
no dietary fiber,

13:36.082 --> 13:39.417
high in the food chain,
so heavily polluted.

13:39.419 --> 13:41.352
- From the standpoint of
the effect of the protein

13:41.354 --> 13:43.555
and fat in those foods,
and their effect on health,

13:43.557 --> 13:44.989
it really doesn't matter.

13:44.991 --> 13:48.092
It's dose dependent,
not type dependent.

13:48.094 --> 13:49.961
So fish is not
healthier, in many cases,

13:49.963 --> 13:54.065
it has more fat, than
chicken and pork.

13:54.067 --> 13:56.000
But you have other
