27:28.814 --> 27:30.748
but mostly fat, he said
that's not the problem,

27:30.750 --> 27:33.083
the problem is we consume
too much carbohydrate.

27:33.085 --> 27:35.052
And he made that point,
we should be consuming

27:35.054 --> 27:36.920
low carb diet, he said.

27:36.922 --> 27:39.790
And then many other people
wrote the same thing.

27:39.792 --> 27:42.960
The south beach diet,
is only a copycat,

27:42.962 --> 27:45.696
for the most part,
of the atkins diet.

27:45.698 --> 27:48.932
The zone diet is basically
a copycat, different name.

27:48.934 --> 27:52.403
The blood type diet in many
regards is also a copycat.

27:52.405 --> 27:55.773
Good calories bad calories,
dairy 12, same thing.

27:55.775 --> 27:59.009
Even Marco paleo, and I have
to say, omnivore's dilemma.

27:59.011 --> 28:00.778
And the paleo diet
in this day and time

28:01.413 --> 28:02.713
is a copycat.

28:03.381 --> 28:03.380
They may give it
different names,

28:03.382 --> 28:07.351
they may try to throw out
you know, different types

28:07.353 --> 28:08.152
of arguments for
why that's right,

28:08.154 --> 28:09.420
they're all wrong.

28:09.422 --> 28:10.888
- Everybody wants
to hear good news

28:10.890 --> 28:12.222
about their bad habits.

28:12.224 --> 28:14.324
So when you tell
people you can eat all

28:14.326 --> 28:17.227
the lobster you want,
you can have steak,

28:17.229 --> 28:19.897
and eggs, and you know,
some include dairy,

28:19.899 --> 28:23.067
some don't include dairy,
but that's sounds good

28:23.069 --> 28:25.903
to people, because it
sounds less restrictive.

28:25.905 --> 28:27.237
- This is written by
people, I should tell you,

28:27.239 --> 28:29.840
who don't have
experience in this field

28:29.842 --> 28:32.309
of nutrition research, period.

28:32.311 --> 28:33.844
Most of them have
never even published

28:33.846 --> 28:36.380
a single paper into
scientific literature.

28:36.382 --> 28:37.815
- Some of the people
who are talking

28:37.817 --> 28:39.817
about low carb diets
are little better than

28:39.819 --> 28:43.153
news reporters, and that's
not to take anything away

28:43.155 --> 28:45.823
from their skill at
investigating things,
but they cannot

28:45.825 --> 28:49.860
don't have the skills to
evaluate scientific information.

28:49.862 --> 28:52.763
- Low carb diets,
they make you sick.

28:52.765 --> 28:55.132
And as a result, your
whole body gets sick,

28:55.134 --> 28:56.967
with artery disease,
and kidney damage,

28:56.969 --> 28:58.402
liver damage and so on.

28:58.404 --> 29:00.170
They increase mortality,
that's been shown

29:00.172 --> 29:03.107
over and over again
in major studies.

29:03.109 --> 29:04.842
But they also make
you sick in a way

29:04.844 --> 29:06.910
that you lose your appetite.

29:06.912 --> 29:09.213
The dieter goes, "oh,
I've finally found it."

29:09.215 --> 29:11.048
And then you go into
ketosis, you lost your

29:11.050 --> 29:14.084
appetite, as a result,
you're able to sustain

29:14.086 --> 29:16.920
yourself without thinking
about food all the time.

29:16.922 --> 29:18.288
Because you're sick.

29:18.290 --> 29:20.891
These diets are dangerous,

29:20.893 --> 29:22.926
and people should
not be on them.

29:22.928 --> 29:24.294
- Well, you know, the
biggest lies in the world

29:24.296 --> 29:27.097
are the ones that
have a little truth.

29:27.099 --> 29:28.132
We all know that.

29:28.134 --> 29:29.900
It's a great tactic.

29:29.902 --> 29:32.369
It's true, I happen to agree,
that we should cut down

29:32.371 --> 29:34.371
on simple carbohydrates.

29:35.507 --> 29:37.808
You see, that's out of
context to the whole.

29:37.810 --> 29:39.510
You know, sugar, white flour.

29:39.512 --> 29:40.978
That makes sense.

29:40.980 --> 29:42.513
So in that sense,
there's a little truth.

29:43.548 --> 29:45.983
But they don't always
point that out.

29:45.985 --> 29:48.285
They just say, low carb,
low carb, low carb.

29:48.287 --> 29:51.021
- Listen, forget about
what you like and dislike,

29:51.023 --> 29:53.323
think about what
your objective is.

29:53.325 --> 29:55.559
Alright, let's just
acknowledge we all like eating

29:55.561 --> 29:55.559
junk food.

29:55.561 --> 29:55.559
If you put chocolate in front
of me today, I'll have some,

29:55.561 --> 30:01.064
right, but that
doesn't lead to health.

30:02.867 --> 30:04.368
- I personally
knew several people

30:04.370 --> 30:06.904
who experienced amazing
healing and health

30:06.906 --> 30:08.872
benefits after
adopting some kind

30:08.874 --> 30:12.376
some kind of a plant-based
diet, including myself.

30:12.378 --> 30:15.579
But at the same time,
i had also met others

30:15.581 --> 30:18.081
who are still experiencing
health issues,

30:18.083 --> 30:20.083
or were struggling
with their weight,

30:20.085 --> 30:24.054
after adopting this lifestyle,
some for many years.

30:24.056 --> 30:25.556
So it made me wonder.

30:25.558 --> 30:27.090
Was there a flaw in this diet?

30:28.560 --> 30:31.461
- First vegetarian
that I knew well

30:31.463 --> 30:34.498
about 40 years ago,
was actually a vegan

30:34.500 --> 30:36.867
he was a very strict vegetarian,

30:36.869 --> 30:40.003
he lived on Coca cola
and potato chips.

30:40.005 --> 30:42.606
He was fat, greasy,
and unhealthy.

30:42.608 --> 30:45.909
So being a vegetarian
means really nothing to me.

30:45.911 --> 30:48.979
- 90% of the vegetarians
are still consuming dairy.

30:48.981 --> 30:50.247
90%.

30:50.249 --> 30:52.316
And they also consume
sometimes some fish,

30:52.318 --> 30:55.552
and sometimes some chicken,
and eggs, and so forth.

30:55.554 --> 30:57.221
The nutrient composition
of the vegetarian diet

30:57.223 --> 31:01.091
is not very different
from the non-vegetarian.

31:02.193 --> 31:04.561
So, as a result, if you compare
the health of vegetarians,

31:04.563 --> 31:07.130
with non-vegetarians, you
can't expect to see very much.

31:07.132 --> 31:09.266
- But somebody's decided
they're going to be vegan,

31:09.268 --> 31:11.535
in other words eat no
animal foods, they've made

31:11.537 --> 31:15.272
a declaration as to
their physical and mental

31:15.274 --> 31:18.275
strength, and their interest,
and their willingness

31:18.277 --> 31:19.443
to work hard.

31:19.445 --> 31:21.979
After all, if you become vegan,

31:21.981 --> 31:24.648
you have to stand up
to your mother-in-law,

31:24.650 --> 31:26.650
and your doctor or your
dietitian, you have to,

31:26.652 --> 31:29.586
quote, risk protein
and calcium deficiency,

31:29.588 --> 31:31.221
even though that's not true.

31:31.223 --> 31:33.090
But the problem is
that too many vegans

31:33.892 --> 31:35.158
they don't look good.

31:35.160 --> 31:37.261
They're overweight,
they're unhealthy looking.

31:37.263 --> 31:39.096
- I don't really like
to use the words vegan

31:39.098 --> 31:41.164
and vegetarian because,

31:42.500 --> 31:44.001
that's not describing
the kind of science

31:44.003 --> 31:45.269
I'm talking about.

31:45.271 --> 31:47.304
- I would call myself a
fat vegan when I first

31:47.306 --> 31:49.573
started out, that's
exactly what I was, and I

31:49.575 --> 31:51.508
was trying to tell
everyone how great this

31:51.510 --> 31:54.111
lifestyle is, and it
saved me, and it reversed

31:54.113 --> 31:55.479
my heart disease.

31:55.481 --> 31:58.548
But yet, I was still walking
around, about 75 pounds

31:58.550 --> 32:00.918
to a hundred pounds overweight.

32:00.920 --> 32:02.352
- Now why is
somebody a fat vegan?

32:03.454 --> 32:06.356
Not because they give
up the animal foods.

32:06.358 --> 32:09.092
That's a good thing, you need
to give up the animal foods.

32:09.094 --> 32:12.029
But what they haven't
given up is the oil.

32:12.031 --> 32:14.231
The olive oil, the
other vegetable oils,

32:14.233 --> 32:18.335
the fat you eat is the
fat you wear, whether

32:18.337 --> 32:20.570
it comes from a
plant, or an animal.

32:20.572 --> 32:22.439
- So, I made the change.

32:22.441 --> 32:24.541
I removed the foods
in my diet that were

32:24.543 --> 32:28.078
empty calories, the
oils and the fats,

32:28.080 --> 32:31.081
the sugars, the processed foods,

32:31.083 --> 32:32.582
the food additives
that kept me coming

32:32.584 --> 32:34.985
back for more, those
companies add those

32:34.987 --> 32:38.055
things purposely to
get us to not eat

32:38.057 --> 32:40.057
just one potato chip.

32:40.059 --> 32:41.591
We need the whole bag.

32:41.593 --> 32:43.961
There's millions of overweight
people in this country,

32:43.963 --> 32:45.662
and they're all struggling,
trying this diet,

32:45.664 --> 32:47.631
or that diet, and they
try this diet for a week,

32:47.633 --> 32:49.599
or that diet for a week,
and they're spending

32:49.601 --> 32:52.602
a lot of money on all these
different diet programs,

32:52.604 --> 32:56.173
and pills, and supplements,
and adding things

32:56.175 --> 32:59.609
to their diet to lose
weight, or to get healthy,

32:59.611 --> 33:02.679
and that's where we need to
realize that a whole foods

33:02.681 --> 33:05.549
plant-based diet is
free, there's no shakes,

33:05.551 --> 33:07.551
there's no bars,
there's no powders,

33:07.553 --> 33:09.653
there's no counting
calories, we eat until

33:09.655 --> 33:12.556
we're full and
satisfied, and stop.

33:12.558 --> 33:14.358
And that's it.

33:14.360 --> 33:16.226
- As much as
i liked the idea of eating

33:16.228 --> 33:18.628
exclusively a plant-based diet,

33:18.630 --> 33:21.164
especially since it
had worked for me,

33:21.166 --> 33:23.033
I wanted this film
to be very accurate

33:23.035 --> 33:25.669
with the latest science on food.

33:25.671 --> 33:28.038
So I wondered, if realistically,

33:28.040 --> 33:30.173
from a scientific perspective,

33:30.175 --> 33:31.575
could every person
in this day and age

33:31.577 --> 33:36.346
eat a plant-based
diet 100% of the time?

33:36.348 --> 33:38.682
- I can't say, and I don't
thing science can say,

33:38.684 --> 33:41.251
that everybody has to be 100%.

33:42.153 --> 33:42.152
You know, all the time.

33:42.154 --> 33:46.490
I can argue the case, i
think, for the vast majority

33:46.492 --> 33:50.093
of people, we ought
to be at least 90,

33:50.095 --> 33:52.429
probably 95%, we've got
good science for that.

33:52.431 --> 33:54.197
And in many cases, if
people already have

33:54.199 --> 33:55.799
a disease, it's a good idea

33:55.801 --> 33:58.201
they should be
100% all the time.

33:58.203 --> 34:00.737
So that's my
scientific argument.

34:00.739 --> 34:02.339
I have another practical
argument, though

34:02.341 --> 34:05.108
on this question, concerning
how far do you go.

34:05.110 --> 34:08.545
And that is that if
we're going to adopt

34:08.547 --> 34:10.179
this dietary lifestyle,

34:12.050 --> 34:15.284
it's really important that
we become accustomed to it.

34:15.286 --> 34:18.255
And we should go
probably 100% if we can.

34:18.257 --> 34:18.255
And stay there.

34:18.257 --> 34:22.192
And don't tease ourselves
with the other things.

34:22.194 --> 34:24.561
Because what happens, we
never become accustomed

34:24.563 --> 34:27.664
to this, where our taste
preferences change.

34:27.666 --> 34:30.266
- If you do it right,
there are no health issues.

34:30.268 --> 34:32.202
In fact, the side effects are
you're going to lose weight,

34:32.204 --> 34:33.703
you're going to look
better, you're going to have

34:33.705 --> 34:36.273
more energy, you're going
to avoid most of the common

34:36.275 --> 34:39.242
degenerative conditions,
most of the time,

34:39.244 --> 34:41.210
you're going to have a
longer life, and a healthier,

34:41.213 --> 34:43.246
and a better life.

34:43.248 --> 34:44.281
You know, that's
about what happens

34:44.283 --> 34:45.215
when you do this.

34:45.217 --> 34:46.716
So there isn't a downside.

34:48.485 --> 34:50.786
- We often hear
that the key to good health

34:50.789 --> 34:53.556
is moderation, and
it makes sense.

34:54.659 --> 34:56.193
But why then does
it not seem to work

34:56.195 --> 34:57.494
for most people?

35:05.436 --> 35:06.670
- You know for some people,

35:06.672 --> 35:08.138
that's a really
easy thing to do.

35:08.140 --> 35:09.739
But unfortunately for most,

35:09.741 --> 35:13.210
finding moderation is
like finding a needle

35:13.212 --> 35:14.344
in a haystack.

35:14.346 --> 35:16.246
And, because others can do it,

35:16.248 --> 35:19.549
they feel lost, and they
feel like an absolute

35:19.551 --> 35:21.284
failure because they can't.

35:21.286 --> 35:23.820
And the truth be
told, most people

35:23.822 --> 35:26.223
can't find moderation,
so they're actually

35:26.225 --> 35:28.458
in the majority and
not the minority.

35:28.460 --> 35:32.262
But this minority few
that are on television,

35:32.264 --> 35:34.898
that have never, ever been fat,

35:34.900 --> 35:36.466
never, ever been sick,

35:36.468 --> 35:39.369
have genetics very
much on their way,

35:39.371 --> 35:40.904
they're out there saying,
"it's all about this,

35:40.906 --> 35:42.372
"and all about that."

35:42.374 --> 35:44.207
I mean, how are
they going to relate

35:44.209 --> 35:46.743
to that poor person
sitting at home,

35:46.745 --> 35:48.678
that's 350 pounds,
that feels like their

35:48.680 --> 35:50.447
world is over?

35:50.449 --> 35:52.349
Now, I know what they feel like.

35:52.351 --> 35:54.584
I was 310 pounds.

35:54.586 --> 35:57.220
I was loaded up on
medication for eight years.

35:57.222 --> 35:59.156
I understand, I can relate.

35:59.158 --> 36:00.790
I won't tell anybody
that moderation's easy.

36:00.792 --> 36:02.726
Moderation's damn hard.

36:02.728 --> 36:04.361
Really hard.

36:04.363 --> 36:05.896
I still haven't mastered it.

36:05.898 --> 36:08.365
I'm a work in progress when
it comes to moderation.

36:08.367 --> 36:11.368
But what I'm finding
is that I'm away

36:11.370 --> 36:12.702
from an extreme now,

36:14.205 --> 36:16.840
of 93% of my energy
coming from this processed

36:16.842 --> 36:18.575
and fun part of
town, animal fat,

36:18.577 --> 36:20.810
I've now got this moderation up,

36:20.812 --> 36:23.613
I've now moved it
up, and it's working.

36:26.517 --> 36:28.285
- So how are
people supposed to get

36:28.287 --> 36:30.220
all this information?

36:30.222 --> 36:32.355
Since everyday we're
bombarded with TV ads,

36:32.357 --> 36:36.326
infomercials, news talking
about the new food trends.

36:36.328 --> 36:38.495
How can we know who's
telling the truth,

36:38.497 --> 36:40.397
and has honest and
unbiased science

36:40.399 --> 36:41.631
behind their products?

36:43.434 --> 36:45.835
- The media always approaches
things with the idea

36:45.837 --> 36:48.572
that if we're going
to interview somebody

36:48.574 --> 36:50.640
about diet, we have to let
somebody with a different

36:50.642 --> 36:53.376
opinion give their opinion.

36:53.378 --> 36:54.945
Alright, so here's what happens.

36:54.947 --> 36:56.846
Someone like Colin Campbell,
at Cornell university

36:56.848 --> 36:59.282
writes this book,
the China study.

36:59.284 --> 36:59.282
It has hundreds and
hundreds and hundreds

36:59.284 --> 37:04.321
of references, it
represents decades of very

37:04.323 --> 37:07.624
meticulous research,
work that he did, right?

37:07.626 --> 37:09.292
And so they're going to
interview him, well then

37:09.294 --> 37:11.394
they go find somebody that's
promoting a paleo diet,

37:11.396 --> 37:13.363
or a low carb diet
because we have to have

37:13.365 --> 37:14.664
the contrary opinion.

37:14.666 --> 37:16.433
That person may have
written a terrible book,

37:16.435 --> 37:17.734
that's a little more
than a storybook,

37:17.736 --> 37:20.570
it's not referenced,
it has no credibility,

37:20.572 --> 37:22.906
but in the eyes of the
public, now those two

37:22.908 --> 37:25.508
are equal, Colin has an opinion,

37:25.510 --> 37:27.510
and this other person
has an opinion.

37:28.679 --> 37:29.679
So it confuses people, and
it gains traction that way.

37:31.315 --> 37:34.451
- We tend to look
at the fast food industry

37:34.453 --> 37:37.254
as the big villain,
responsible for all the havoc

37:37.256 --> 37:38.688
surrounding food choices.

37:39.790 --> 37:41.458
But these same companies
that are contributing

37:41.460 --> 37:44.327
to the problem may
also hold the key

37:44.329 --> 37:45.962
to the solution.

37:45.964 --> 37:48.031
It is a supply and demand issue,

37:48.033 --> 37:50.867
so if enough people
begin demanding healthy,

37:50.869 --> 37:54.804
plant-based options, perhaps
that could be a good approach.

37:54.806 --> 37:57.574
After all, it is us the
consumers who should dictate

37:57.576 --> 37:59.909
what the market has to offer.

37:59.911 --> 38:01.511
And not the other way around.

38:02.913 --> 38:06.483
- You can make better,
cleaner, healthier products

38:06.485 --> 38:08.818
by incorporating more
plant-based foods

38:08.820 --> 38:11.888
into your products, and
not to shy away from that.

38:11.890 --> 38:13.790
So, I don't take a
negative approach like down

38:13.792 --> 38:16.393
with these fast foods.

38:16.395 --> 38:18.728
We need to make them understand

38:18.730 --> 38:20.530
that they can still
make money, and they

38:20.532 --> 38:22.499
can still have a
sustainable business,

38:22.501 --> 38:24.067
because there are
people out there

38:24.069 --> 38:25.535
that want this food.

38:25.537 --> 38:27.737
We just have to make
it available to them.

38:37.448 --> 38:38.648
- Most people
rely on their doctors

38:38.650 --> 38:41.718
for information about
diet and nutrition.

38:41.720 --> 38:43.753
But several medical
school programs

38:43.755 --> 38:48.325
show that doctors get very
little training on nutrition.

38:48.327 --> 38:50.026
Sometimes, none at all.

38:51.929 --> 38:53.463
- As I went through
medical school,

38:53.465 --> 38:55.865
and I went through
residency, and I started

38:57.001 --> 39:00.470
after that, working on
my own as a physician,

39:00.472 --> 39:04.341
after awhile, I became kind
of a little bit frustrated

39:04.343 --> 39:06.509
with my inability to
really, really help people.

39:06.511 --> 39:07.944
Because what i
thought was happening,

39:07.946 --> 39:11.548
was that, I was just
basically seeing patients,

39:11.550 --> 39:13.683
asked to see them very quickly,

39:13.685 --> 39:15.452
and was really left
with limited options

39:15.454 --> 39:17.120
as far as what I could do.

39:17.122 --> 39:19.556
I really felt what i
needed to do with the time

39:19.558 --> 39:22.492
that I had, was left to
do, was just basically

39:22.494 --> 39:26.096
treat symptoms, instead of
trying to get to the root cause

39:26.098 --> 39:27.931
of the problem, or the root
cause of their disease.

39:27.933 --> 39:30.567
So, it left me basically
practicing I think the kind

39:30.569 --> 39:33.470
of medicine that the
majority of people are

39:33.472 --> 39:36.573
practicing in the U.S.,
which is pharmaceutical based

39:36.575 --> 39:39.476
medicine, and I don't have
a problem with medication.

39:39.478 --> 39:41.044
I think medications are
wonderful, medications

39:41.046 --> 39:44.547
are great, they're necessary
for a lot of people,

39:44.549 --> 39:45.982
they are really the only option.

39:45.984 --> 39:48.485
For many people
they're a good option.

39:48.487 --> 39:50.587
But I think what we're
missing is that there's

39:50.589 --> 39:52.489
something else that's out there.

39:53.691 --> 39:56.726
- I was outsourcing my
health, to somebody else.

39:56.728 --> 39:58.561
I was coming along saying,
"here's some money,

39:58.563 --> 40:01.097
"will you fix me,
I'm busy over here."

40:01.099 --> 40:02.565
And when are you
going to come up

40:02.567 --> 40:04.100
with a drug that's
going to like, cure me?

40:05.169 --> 40:08.004
- By using more
chemicals to correct

40:08.006 --> 40:10.173
the imbalance, we're
actually causing

40:10.175 --> 40:13.476
the imbalances to
be even stronger.

40:13.478 --> 40:16.513
I found that people
who've been on medications

40:16.515 --> 40:20.583
for a long time, are developing
a lot of side effects

40:20.585 --> 40:22.585
from those medications,
where then are causing

40:22.587 --> 40:26.956
other organs in their
bodies to become diseased,

40:28.159 --> 40:31.161
their functioning is
weakening, their overall health

